# `{{ stack_name }}` stack

One independently-deployed Terraform unit. All three environments deploy into the
single `whimsyhollow` project; their state is partitioned by GCS prefix in the one
shared bucket (`gs://whimsyhollow-tfstate/terraform/state/<env>/{{ stack_name }}`).
The same `*.tf` files plan/apply against any environment via partial backend
configuration — switch envs by changing the backend config at `init` time and
`-var environment=<env>` at `plan` time.

## Quickstart

Via the `tfs` CLI (recommended — it wires the `-chdir`, backend config, and
`-var environment` flags for you, and adds a `gcloud` project guardrail):

```sh
tfs init  {{ stack_name }} dev
tfs plan  {{ stack_name }} dev
tfs apply {{ stack_name }} dev
```

Or drive `terraform` directly from `infra/`:

```sh
terraform -chdir=stacks/{{ stack_name }} init  -backend-config=./backends/<env>.config -reconfigure
terraform -chdir=stacks/{{ stack_name }} plan  -var environment=<env>
terraform -chdir=stacks/{{ stack_name }} apply -var environment=<env>
```

## QA

```sh
make -C infra STACK={{ stack_name }} validate-dev   # init + validate against dev's backend
make -C infra fmt-check                             # terraform fmt -check (all stacks)
make -C infra docs                                  # regenerate the tf-docs block below
```

## CI/CD

This stack is deployed by `.github/workflows/terraform-cicd-stack-{{ stack_name }}.yml`,
a thin per-stack caller (auto-generated by `tfs create`) that forwards to
the shared reusable workflow `.github/workflows/terraform-cicd-per-stack.yml`.

| Git event | Terraform action |
|-----------|------------------|
| 🏚️ Draft PR (this stack's paths) | `fmt` + `validate` + `plan` (dev/test/prod) |
| 🏡 Ready-for-review PR | the above, then `apply` → **dev** |
| 🚀 Push to `main` | `apply` → **test** |
| 🏷️ Push tag `v*` / `workflow_dispatch` | `apply` → **prod** |

By design prod is only ever reached by a release tag or a manual dispatch — never
a branch push.

